Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "nasilje" in different forms and positions:

1. *Nasilje* je neprihvatljivo ponašanje. (Violence is unacceptable behavior.)
2. Svedok sam *nasilja* koje se desilo sinoć. (I witnessed the *violence* that occurred last night.)
3. Oni su izvršili *nasilje* nad žrtvama. (They committed *violence* against the victims.)
4. Prijavila sam *nasilje* policiji. (I reported *violence* to the police.)
5. *Nasilništvo* se mora sprečiti. (Violent behavior must be prevented.)
6. Ovakvo *nasilje* neće biti tolerisano. (This kind of *violence* will not be tolerated.)
7. Nasilje u porodici je ozbiljan problem. (Domestic violence is a serious problem.)
8. Žrtva *nasilja* može da potraži pomoć. (A victim of *violence* can seek help.)
9. Borimo se protiv *nasilja* u školama. (We are fighting against *violence* in schools.)
10. Učesnici su se sukobili, ali nije bilo fizičkog *nasilja*. (The participants clashed, but there was no physical *violence*.)

I hope these sentences help!